------
FILE SYSTEM STRUCTURE
------

/boot   - contains file that is used by the boot loeader (grub.cfg)
/root   - root user home directory.
/dev    - system devices (disk, cdrom...)
/etc    - configuration files
/bin    - everyday user commands
/sbin   - system/filesystem commands
/opt    - optional add-on applications
/proc   - running processes (only in memory)
/lib    - c programming library files needed by commands and applications
/tmp    - directory for temporary files
/home   - directory for user
/var    - system logs
/run    - system daemons that start very early (systemd, udev)
/mnt    - mount external filesystem 
/media  - for cdrom mounts 

